How does counting algorithm work?

- stores buffer of 5 frames but esp can't 'push' a new value onto an array, 
    so it overrites oldest with new. Like frame1,2,3 then frame4,2,3 then frame4,5,3
    it uses a HEAD pointer variable know that (e.g.) '3' is the oldest, so start there
    this is called a ring buffer

- counts the NUMBER of the grid column (1-5) in newest and oldest frame. 
    a left to right cross might be newest column - oldest column = 2
    a right to left corss might be newest column - oldest column = -3